-- Ukraine’s Kernel May Spend $100 Million on Russia Sunflower Mill
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-02-16T05:57:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/ukraine-s-kernel-may-spend-100-million-on-russia-sunflower-mill.html
Kernel Holding SA (KER) , Ukraine’s Warsaw-
listed sunflower-oil producer, plans to spend $100 million to
build a crushing plant in  Russia  over the next two years,
according to its fourth-quarter report.  The plant will have an annual capacity to process 600,000
metric tons of sunflower seeds into oil, the report shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
